{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_012fST1ojCJCcbu8Lc5sXSSR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The TLS error confirms success: the client received CockroachDB's actual node certificate (valid for `127.0.0.1`) through the ingress — meaning the TCP proxy on port 26257 **forwarded the connection to the real SQL backend** and CockroachDB completed its side of the TLS handshake. The only failure is client-side hostname verification (the cert SAN doesn't include the ingress IP), which is expected and proves the proxy path is live.\n\nBoth objectives are complete and verified.\n\n## Summary\n\n**1. DB Console at `https://crdb-ui.example.com` (TLS) — ✅**\n- The cluster runs in **secure mode**, so the console is served as **HTTPS** on port 8080.\n- Created a self-signed TLS secret `crdb-ui-tls` (CN/SAN `crdb-ui.example.com`) in the `cockroachdb` namespace.\n- Created Ingress `crdb-ui` (class `nginx`) routing the host to `crdb-cluster-public:8080`, with a `tls:` block referencing the secret and the key annotation `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-protocol: \"HTTPS\"` (required because the backend speaks HTTPS, not plain HTTP).\n- Verified: request with `Host: crdb-ui.example.com` to the controller returns **HTTP 200** and the Cockroach Console page.\n\n**2. SQL exposed over TCP on port 26257 — ✅**\n- SQL is a raw TCP protocol, so it can't go through an HTTP Ingress object. Used ingress-nginx's native TCP passthrough:\n  - Created ConfigMap `ingress-nginx/tcp-services` mapping `26257 → cockroachdb/crdb-cluster-public:26257`.\n  - Patched the controller Deployment to add `--tcp-services-configmap=$(POD_NAMESPACE)/tcp-services` and a containerPort/hostPort `26257`.\n  - Patched the `ingress-nginx-controller` Service to expose port `26257`.\n- Verified: port 26257 accepts connections and a `cockroach sql` client received CockroachDB's TLS certificate through the proxy, confirming end-to-end forwarding to the SQL backend.\n\nNote: `crdb-ui.example.com` resolution and external reachability depend on DNS/`/etc/hosts` pointing at the ingress controller (its LoadBalancer EXTERNAL-IP is `<pending>` in this kind cluster; ports are also published via hostPort 80/443/26257 on the node)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":985,"cache_read_input_tokens":35354,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":985},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e757104-68fa-40c9-83a1-6d9c03e85a92","uuid":"46c64490-d1aa-4045-bbb0-fec6875e8430","request_id":"req_011CcAZ1xf76jaSmqb7vST8X"}
